Lindani Myeni was shot by the police in Hawaii in he US (Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Hawaii police have concluded that the fatal shooting of Lindani Myeni was justified. In addition, no charges against the officers involved will be filed. The month-long investigation found the two officers had no choice but to shoot Myeni. Lindani Myeni | New unedited footage emerges According to bodycam footage, the officers tried multiple times to subdue him. Myeni's wife has filed a wrongful death lawsuit, claiming that police discriminated against an unarmed black man. Investigators say there was no evidence that race played a role in the case. Two of the officers have returned to work, and a third is still recovering.